The paper proposes a method for automatic and objective characterization of clusters obtained by mixture models, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining. The paper also discusses the interpretation and evaluation of the mined results, which are important topics in the fields of artificial intelligence and data management. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Data Mining). Additionally, the paper deals with datasets that include continuous attributes and missing values, which are common issues in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
